== Preparation ==

Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips
and chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces.

Halve the @premium tomato mix{125}. Remove and discard the bottom 2cm of stalk 
from the @asparagus{200%g}. Chop widthways into thirds.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Finely chop the 
@sun-dried tomatoes{30%g}. Put your #kettle{} on to boil.

== Grilling the Vegetables ==

Pop the aubergine and plum tomatoes onto a lined #baking tray{}. Add a drizzle 
of @oil{some} and a sprinkle of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss together to evenly coat
in the seasoning then arrange in a single layer.

Pop the tray on the top shelf of your #oven{} and grill until soft and starting 
to colour, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

== Sauce ==

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{some} in a large #frying pan{} on medium
heat. Add the sun-dried tomatoes and @chilli flakes{1/4} (just a pinch, these 
flakes are HOT). Cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Pasta ==

Pour the water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} and bring back to the 
boil. Add the @wholewheat spaghetti{150%g} and a good pinch of @salt{}. Cook for
~{7%minutes} then add the asparagus.

Continue to cook the spaghetti and asparagus for a further ~{4%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{} then return to the pan off the heat. Drizzle over a 
little @oil{some} to stop the spaghetti sticking together.

While the spaghetti cooks, add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and 
garlic{1} to the frying pan along with a good grind of @pepper{}. Let the 
mixture bubble away on medium heat until the sauce is nice and thick, stirring
occasionally, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the grilled aubergine and plum tomatoes 
and half the parsley. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if necessary.

== Assembly ==

Tip the spaghetti into the sauce and gently stir together until everything is 
nicely combined.

Serve in bowls, sprinkle over the remaining parsley and tuck in! ENJOY!

